_and_slavery"}
{"title_page": "List of current champions in WWE", "text_new": "{{pp-semi|small=yes}}\n{{short description|Listing of championships currently utilized by American professional wrestling promotion WWE}}\n{{use mdy dates|date=October 2018}}\n[[WWE]] is an American [[professional wrestling]] [[Professional wrestling promotion|promotion]] based out of [[Stamford, Connecticut|Stamford]], [[Connecticut]]. Title reigns are either determined by [[Professional wrestling match types|professional wrestling matches]] or are awarded to a wrestler, as a result of the culmination of various scripted [[Kayfabe|storylines]].\n\nWWE promotes three primary [[WWE brand extension|brands]] \u2013 [[Raw (WWE brand)|Raw]], [[SmackDown (WWE brand)|SmackDown]], and [[NXT (WWE brand)|NXT]].<ref>[http://www.wwe.com/shows/wwenxt/article/nxt-moves-to-usa-network NXT moves to USA Network - WWE.com]</ref> Specialty brands in WWE include [[205 Live (WWE brand)|205 Live]] \u2013 for male wrestlers 205 lbs. and under (designated by WWE as [[Cruiserweight (professional wrestling)|cruiserweights]]) \u2013 and [[NXT UK (WWE brand)|NXT UK]], which is for wrestlers based in the [[United Kingdom]].\n\nRaw, SmackDown, and NXT each have a primary and secondary championship for male wrestlers, a singles championship for female wrestlers, and a tag team championship for male wrestlers. There is also one tag team championship for female wrestlers that is shared between the three brands. There is one championship for the cruiserweight wrestlers that is shared between NXT, NXT UK, and 205 Live, which is the only championship with a weight limit in the promotion, and one male singles, one female singles, and one male tag team championship for NXT UK wrestlers. There is also one tertiary championship, which is accessible to anyone, regardless of gender or WWE status.\n\nThere are currently 18 championships in WWE. Among the five current brands, 23 wrestlers hold the championships as of {{CURRENTMONTHNAME}} {{CURRENTDAY}}, {{CURRENTYEAR}}. The list includes the number of times the wrestler has held the title, the date and location of the win, and a description of the winning bout.\n\n== Current champions ==\n;Men's singles\nAt the top of [[WWE]]'s championship hierarchy for male wrestlers are the [[WWE Championship]] on [[Raw (WWE brand)|Raw]], the [[WWE Universal Championship|Universal Championship]] on [[SmackDown (WWE brand)|SmackDown]], and the [[NXT Championship]] on [[NXT (WWE brand)|NXT]] \u2014 all designated as [[Professional wrestling championship#World championships|world championships]]. The WWE Champion is [[Drew McIntyre]], who is in his first reign. He won the title by defeating [[Brock Lesnar]] during [[WrestleMania 36]] Part 2 that aired on [[Broadcast delay|tape delay]] on April 5, 2020 (the event was taped on March 25 and 26, though it is currently unknown which day this match took place).<ref>{{cite web|title=WWE Championship|url=http://www.wwe.com/classics/titlehistory/wwe-championship|publisher=[[WWE]]|accessdate=January 3, 2020}}</ref> The Universal Championship is held by [[Braun Strowman]], who is in his first reign. He won the title by defeating [[Bill Goldberg|Goldberg]] during [[WrestleMania 36]] Part 1 that aired on [[Broadcast delay|tape delay]] on April 4, 2020 (the event was taped on March 25 and 26, though it is currently unknown which day this match took place).<ref>{{cite web|title=Universal Championship|url=http://www.wwe.com/classics/titlehistory/universal-championship|publisher=[[WWE]]|accessdate=January 3, 2020}}</ref> The NXT Championship is held by [[Adam Cole]], who is in his first reign. He won the title by defeating [[Johnny Gargano]] at [[NXT TakeOver: XXV|TakeOver: XXV]] on June 1, 2019.<ref>{{cite web|title=NXT Championship|url=http://www.wwe.com/classics/titlehistory/nxt-championship|publisher=[[WWE]]|accessdate=January 3, 2020}}</ref>\n\n[[Professional wrestling championship#Location-specific championships|Secondary titles]] for male wrestlers include the [[WWE United States Championship|United States Championship]] on Raw, the [[WWE Intercontinental Championship|Intercontinental Championship]] on SmackDown, and the [[NXT North American Championship|North American Championship]] on NXT. The United States Championship is held by [[Andrade (wrestler)|Andrade]], who is in his first reign. He won the title by defeating [[Rey Mysterio]] at a [[WWE Live]] event on December 26, 2019.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.wwe.com/classics/titlehistory/unitedstates/|title=United States Championship|publisher=[[WWE]]|accessdate=January 3, 2020}}</ref> The Intercontinental Championship is held by [[Sami Zayn]], who is in his first reign. He won the title by defeating [[Braun Strowman]] in a [[Handicap match|3-on-1 Handicap match]] also featuring [[Cesaro (wrestler)|Cesaro]] and [[Shinsuke Nakamura]] as Zayn's partners on  March 8, 2020 at [[Elimination Chamber (2020)|Elimination Chamber]]\u2014Zayn won the title since he pinned Strowman. The North American Championship is held by first-time title holder [[Keith Lee (wrestler)|Keith Lee]], who defeated [[Roderick Strong]] on the January 22, 2020 episode of ''[[WWE NXT|NXT]]''.<ref>{{cite web|title=NXT North American Championship|url=http://www.wwe.com/classics/titlehistory/nxt-north-american-championship|publisher=[[WWE]]|accessdate=January 3, 2020}}</ref>\n\n;Men's tag team\n[[World tag team championship|Tag team championships]] for male wrestlers include the [[WWE Raw Tag Team Championship|Raw Tag Team Championship]], the [[WWE SmackDown Tag Team Championship|SmackDown Tag Team Championship]], and the [[NXT Tag Team Championship]]. The Raw Tag Team Championship is held by [[The Street Profits]] (Angelo Dawkins and Montez Ford), who are in their first reign as a team and individually. They won the title by defeating [[Seth Rollins]] and [[Buddy Murphy|Murphy]] in a [[Professional wrestling match types#Last Chance match|last chance match]] on the March 2, 2020 episode of ''[[Monday Night Raw]]''.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.wwe.com/classics/titlehistory/raw-tag-team-championship|title=Raw Tag Team Championship|publisher=[[WWE]]|accessdate=January 3, 2020}}</ref> The SmackDown Tag Team Championship is held by [[The New Day (professional wrestling)|The New Day]] ([[Big E (wrestler)|Big E]], [[Xavier Woods]] and [[Kofi Kingston]]), who are in their record sixth reign as a group; individually Big E has been in all six reigns, while Kingston and Woods each have been in five. The group generally invoke the [[Freebird rule]], which allows for any two members to defend the title, though Kingston was not recognized as champion during the fourth reign, as he was the then-current WWE Champion, and Woods was not recognized during the fifth reign, as he was inactive due to an injury. Big E won the titles for his team by defeating previous co-champion [[The Miz]] (who held the titles with [[John Morrison (wrestler)|John Morrison]]) and [[Jey Uso]] in a triple threat match on April 17, 2020 during the live broadcast of ''SmackDown''. The NXT Tag Team Championship is held by The BroserWeights ([[Matt Riddle]] and [[Pete Dunne]]), who are in their first reign. They defeated [[The Undisputed Era]]'s [[Bobby Fish]] and [[Kyle O'Reilly]] at [[NXT TakeOver: Portland|TakeOver: Portland]] on February 16, 2020.\n\n;Specialty\nThe [[WWE 24/7 Championship]] is a tertiary championship shared across all five brands and is open to anyone regardless of gender (including non-WWE personnel). It can be defended anytime, [[Falls Count Anywhere match|anywhere]], as long as a WWE referee is present. The current champion is [[Rob Gronkowski]], who is in his first reign. He won the title by pinning [[Mojo Rawley]] in-front of the host's podium during [[WrestleMania 36]] Part 2 that aired on [[tape delay]] on April 5, 2020 (the event was taped on March 25 and 26, though it is currently unknown which day this title change took place)\u2014Gronkowski is a former [[NFL]] player who had recently signed with WWE and served as the host of WrestleMania 36.\n\nThe [[NXT Cruiserweight Championship]] is the only championship of the [[205 Live (WWE brand)|205 Live]] brand and is also defended on NXT and NXT UK. It is for wrestlers {{convert|205|lb|kg|abbr=on}} and under (referred to as [[Cruiserweight (professional wrestling)|cruiserweights]]); the only championship in WWE with a [[Professional wrestling championship#Weight class championships|weight limit]]. The title is held by [[Jordan Devlin]] from NXT UK, who is in his first reign. He won the title by defeating former champion [[Angel Garza]], [[Travis Banks]], and [[Isaiah \"Swerve\" Scott]], who Devlin pinned, in a [[fatal four-way match]] at [[Worlds Collide (2020)|Worlds Collide]] on January 25, 2020.<ref>{{cite web|title=NXT Cruiserweight Championship|url=http://www.wwe.com/classics/titlehistory/nxt-cruiserweight-championship|publisher=[[WWE]]|accessdate=January 3, 2020}}</ref> Due to a travel ban as a result of the [[2019\u201320 coronavirus pandemic]], Devlin is unable to defend the title. A tournament will be held to crown an interim champion until his return.\n\n;Women's\nAt the top of WWE's championship hierarchy for female wrestlers are the [[WWE Raw Women's Championship|Raw Women's Championship]], the [[WWE SmackDown Women's Championship|SmackDown Women's Championship]], and the [[NXT Women's Championship]] \u2014 all designated as world championships. The Raw Women's Championship is held by [[Becky Lynch]], who is in her first reign. She won the title in a [[Professional wrestling match types#Winner Takes All match|Winner Takes All]] [[Professional wrestling match types#Basic non-elimination matches|triple threat match]] involving former champion [[Ronda Rousey]] and [[Charlotte Flair]] (who defended the SmackDown Women's Championship) at [[WrestleMania 35]] on April 8, 2019.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.wwe.com/classics/titlehistory/raw-womens-championship|title=Raw Women's Championship|publisher=[[WWE]]|accessdate=January 3, 2020}}</ref> The SmackDown Women's Championship is held by [[Bayley (wrestler)|Bayley]], who is in her second reign. She won the title by defeating [[Charlotte Flair]] on ''[[SmackDown]]'' on October 11, 2019.<ref>{{cite web|title=SmackDown Women's Championship|url=http://www.wwe.com/classics/titlehistory/smackdown-womens-championship|publisher=[[WWE]]|accessdate=January 3, 2020}}</ref> The NXT Women's Championship is held by [[Charlotte Flair]], who is in her second reign. She won the title by defeating [[Rhea Ripley]] during [[WrestleMania 36]] Part 2 that aired on [[tape delay]] on April 5, 2020 (the event was taped on March 25 and 26, though it is currently unknown which day this match took place).<ref>{{cite web|title=NXT Women's Championship|url=http://www.wwe.com/classics/titlehistory/nxt-womens-championship|publisher=[[WWE]]|accessdate=January 3, 2020}}</ref>\n\nThe [[WWE Women's Tag Team Championship|Women's Tag Team Championship]] is the only tag team championship for female wrestlers in WWE, and is shared between the Raw, SmackDown, and NXT brands.<ref name=\"AllBrands\">{{cite web|url=https://www.wwe.com/shows/raw/article/wwe-womens-tag-team-championships-defend-raw-smackdown-live-nxt|title=WWE Women\u2019s Tag Team Championships to be defended across Raw, SmackDown LIVE and NXT|date=February 18, 2019|last=Benigno|first=Anthony|work=WWE.com|accessdate=February 19, 2019}}</ref> It is held by [[Alexa Bliss]] and [[Nikki Cross]] from SmackDown, who are in their record second reign. They won the title by defeating The Kabuki Warriors ([[Asuka (wrestler)|Asuka]] and [[Kairi Sane]]) during [[WrestleMania 36]] Part 1 that aired on [[tape delay]] on April 4, 2020 (the event was taped on March 25 and 26, though it is currently unknown which day this match took place).<ref>{{cite web|title=WWE Women's Tag Team Championship|url=http://www.wwe.com/classics/titlehistory/wwe-womens-tag-team-championship|publisher=[[WWE]]|accessdate=January 3, 2020}}</ref> \n\n;UK\nThe top title of [[NXT UK (WWE brand)|NXT UK]] is the [[NXT United Kingdom Championship]]. It is held by [[Walter (wrestler)|Walter]], who is in his first reign. He won the title by defeating [[Pete Dunne (wrestler)|Pete Dunne]] at [[NXT TakeOver: New York|TakeOver: New York]] on April 5, 2019, ending Dunne's reign at 685 days.<ref>{{cite web|title=WWE United Kingdom Championship|url=http://www.wwe.com/classics/titlehistory/wwe-united-kingdom-championship|publisher=[[WWE]]|accessdate=January 3, 2020}}</ref> The [[NXT UK Women's Championship]] is held by first-time title holder [[Kay Lee Ray]], who won the title by defeating [[Toni Storm]] at [[NXT UK TakeOver: Cardiff|TakeOver: Cardiff]] on August 31, 2019.<ref>{{cite web|title=NXT UK Women's Championship|url=http://www.wwe.com/classics/titlehistory/nxt-uk-womens-championship|publisher=[[WWE]]|accessdate=January 3, 2020}}</ref> The [[NXT UK Tag Team Championship]] is held by Gallus ([[Mark Coffey]] and [[Wolfgang (wrestler)|Wolfgang]]), who are in their first reign. They defeated [[Mark Andrews (wrestler)|Mark Andrews]] and [[Morgan Webster|Flash Morgan Webster]] on October 4, 2019 during the ''[[NXT UK]]'' tapings ([[Broadcast delay|aired]] October 17).<ref>{{cite web|title=NXT UK Tag Team Championship|url=http://www.wwe.com/classics/titlehistory/nxt-uk-tag-team-championship|publisher=[[WWE]]|accessdate=January 3, 2020}}</ref>\n\n=== Raw ===\n{| class=\"wikitable\" style=\"font-size: 85%;\"\n|-\n!Championship\n!colspan=2 | Current champion(s)\n!Reign\n!Date won \n!Days<br />held\n!Location\n!Notes\n|-\n|align=center | [[WWE Championship]]\n|align=center | [[File:Drew Galloway March 2017.jpg|100px]]\n|align=center | [[Drew McIntyre]]\n|align=center | 1\n|align=center | March 25 or 26, 2020\n|align=center | {{age in days nts|March 25, 2020}} or {{age in days nts|March 26, 2020}}\n|align=center | [[Orlando, Florida]]\n|Defeated [[Brock Lesnar]] during 